Analyze the overall supply chain to identify risk and drive resolution to systemic supply chain issues affecting quality, cost, delivery or lead-times. 
Partner with internal stakeholders to develop and implement strategic sourcing strategies in support of the long-range plans. 
Develop negotiation strategy and approach, acceptable terms and conditions and lead the Facebook negotiation team through to closure. 
RF-x Services: Own the interface to and lead engagement with suppliers for all RFI, RFP and RFQ activities. 
Support should cost and/or market and actual unit and total cost data which feeds into total cost of ownership (TCO) models. 
Drive continuous supplier improvement in purchase price and total cost, including supply chain performance cost. 
Measure, report and action cost improvement as compared to market pricing. 
Supplier development and management: Manage the overall supplier relationship and lead and coordinate efforts to drive supplier performance improvement in all areas. 
Lead measuring supplier performance (OTD, Cost, availability, etc.), root cause issues, and driving improved performance. Own all aspects of supplier performance. 
Act as the primary liaison between ODM supplier and Facebook teams monitoring, managing and driving the supplier to assure build goals/schedule is being met. 
Communicate forecast and verify fulfillment from a materials perspective. 
Propose and execute solutions to eliminate shortages impacting build and ship schedules. 
Interactions involve strategic and tactical procurement activities in a global environment. 
BA/BS in ME, EE, CE, CS, Business, Supply Chain Management or equivalent years of experience 
